\begin_layout Standard
The aim of this report is to evaluate the performance of a regression model
 when the number of coefficients (
\begin_inset Formula $\beta$
\end_inset

) is close to the number of samples.
 We will employ various criteria to identify the best model that provides
 an optimal balance between the model's complexity and its predictive power.
 We will compare and analyze the results obtained from each criterion to
 determine which one performs best.
\end_layout

