\begin_layout Standard
In the first task we create design matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 (
\begin_inset Formula $1000\times950$
\end_inset

) which elements are iid random variables from 
\begin_inset Formula $N\br{0,\frac{1}{\sqrt{1000}}}$
\end_inset

 then generate vector 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Y=X\beta+\epsilon
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta=\br{3,3,3,3,3,3,0,\ldots,0}^{T}$
\end_inset

and 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon\sim N\br{0,I}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For each of the considered model, we estimate 
\series bold

\begin_inset Formula $\beta$
